OL,3,CTriathlete could have bled to death
OL,4,Cbefore treatment for rare illness
OL,6,FA blood test showed Ollie had around
OL,7,F13,000 platelets, significantly lower
OL,8,Fthan the average of up to 450,000.
OL,10,FPlatelets are cell segments which help
OL,11,Fblood clot and stop bleeding at the
OL,12,Fsite of a cut - without them, a person
OL,13,Fwould bleed uncontrollably.
OL,15,FOllie told ITV News he is grateful
OL,16,Fthat Georgia, who is a nurse, booked
OL,17,Fhis GP appointment and potentially
OL,18,Fsaved his life.
